WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:11.624
Welcome to the Reports tutorial. The public demo builds a portable Markdown summary from the active in-memory incident without creating report history.

2
00:00:13.024 --> 00:00:22.000
We load the sanitized SSH sample. The selected incident, its four findings, and linked evidence define the report scope.

3
00:00:23.400 --> 00:00:33.576
The control panel shows the active incident and available format. Public mode supports Markdown only, and opening this view does not generate anything.

4
00:00:34.976 --> 00:00:44.120
We enable redaction. The next report masks IP addresses, users, and hosts while leaving the analysis result unchanged.

5
00:00:45.520 --> 00:00:55.240
We click Generate report. TraceHawk creates an in-memory preview; it does not persist a server-side report or download a file automatically.

6
00:00:56.640 --> 00:01:08.568
We review evidence, conclusions, recommendations, and redaction in the preview. Download dot M D becomes available only after generation and saves the reviewed content locally.
